		<title>On-the-fly assembling</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://www.messylab.com/component/content/article/6-front-page/6-on-the-fly-assembling"/>
		<published>2010-07-26T16:59:49Z</published>
		<updated>2010-07-26T16:59:49Z</updated>
		<id>http://www.messylab.com/component/content/article/6-front-page/6-on-the-fly-assembling</id>
		<author>
			<name>Miloš Anđelković</name>
		<email>drstorm@messylab.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;The code editor features&amp;nbsp;On-the-fly&amp;nbsp;assembling of the source code which means that the your code is being processed as you type.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The generated machine code is displayed along side with the source code, making it easy to see the direct link that exists between the symbolic representation of the machine code (i.e. the source code)&amp;nbsp;and its actual binary form.&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;The code editor features&amp;nbsp;On-the-fly&amp;nbsp;assembling of the source code which means that the your code is being processed as you type.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The generated machine code is displayed along side with the source code, making it easy to see the direct link that exists between the symbolic representation of the machine code (i.e. the source code)&amp;nbsp;and its actual binary form.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
